  init_keywords;
  writeln(kw_len(0));
  print_keyword(129); writeln(0);
  print_operator(167); writeln(0);
  print_variable(192); writeln(0);
  { Adding these causes the hang: }
  if kw_len(0) = 3 then write('P') else write('F'); writeln(1);
  if kw_len(1) = 5 then write('P') else write('F'); writeln(2);
  if kw_len(3) = 2 then write('P') else write('F'); writeln(3);
  if kw_len(7) = 6 then write('P') else write('F'); writeln(4);
  if is_keyword(128) then write('P') else write('F'); writeln(5);
  if is_variable(192) then write('P') else write('F'); writeln(6);
  if var_index(217) = 25 then write('P') else write('F'); writeln(7);
  if var_index(192) = 0 then write('P') else write('F'); writeln(8)
end.
```

Compile:
```bash
printf '%s\x04' "$(cat test.pas)" | \
  cor24-run --run compiler/p24p.s --terminal --speed 0 -n 500000000 2>&1
```

## Bisection results

| Main block statements | Lines | Instructions | Result |
|----------------------|-------|-------------|--------|
| 7 (base)             | 147   | 39M         | ✅ OK  |
| +5 if/writeln pairs  | 153   | 42M         | ✅ OK  |
| +6                   | 154   | 42M         | ✅ OK  |
| +7                   | 156   | 43M         | ✅ OK  |
| +8                   | 158   | >200M       | ❌ hangs |
| +10                  | 163   | >200M       | ❌ hangs |

The cliff is sharp — 7 extra statement pairs compile at 43M instructions, 8 pairs never finish (tested to 12B instructions / 2 minutes wall time).

## Likely cause

Suspect quadratic or exponential blowup in symbol table lookup or code emission. With 12 user procedures + 14 system procs + 10 constants + array globals + procedure locals/params, the symbol table is near its MAX_SYMBOLS=64 limit. Each additional statement in the main block may trigger increasingly expensive lookups.

## Impact

**Blocking sw-cor24-basic** — the BASIC interpreter will be 500+ lines of Pascal with 20+ procedures. The current ~155-line / 12-procedure limit makes it impossible to build the interpreter as a single program. Either:
1. Fix the performance cliff (preferred)
2. Increase MAX_SYMBOLS and optimize symbol lookup
3. Add multi-file compilation support so the interpreter can be split

## Environment

- p24p compiled by tc24r, running on cor24-run emulator
- All individual language features work fine in isolation
- The issue is strictly size/complexity dependent
